id: pm-rmjy
title: "MCP pm_list/pm_search: expose active filter summary in compact output so agents know what was applied"
description: "When an agent calls pm_list with options.status='open' and options.type='Feature', the compact output already includes a `filters` section (from runList). But via the narrow pm_list tool, filters are nested inside `options: {}` with no top-level declaration, so the unexpected-key warning system (pm-qxwu) doesn't validate them, and the MCP tool description does not list the available filter keys. This creates a discoverability gap: agents must either call pm_run or read the option description prose. Adding a `query_summary` field in structuredContent.result that echoes back the resolved filters and projection mode would close the feedback loop."
type: Feature
status: open
priority: 3
tags[3]: agent-ux,"area:mcp",dx
created_at: "2026-06-07T10:04:09.891Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-07T10:22:12.728Z"
author: audit-platform-agent
acceptance_criteria: "- pm_list/pm_search compact MCP output includes an applied-filters summary\n- Agents can see which filters were applied without re-echoing inputs\n- Covered by a contract/snapshot test"
